'}, {'user_id': 'syohex', 'created_at': '2016-05-31T03:38:33Z', 'comment_text': 'BTW for Autoware developers, there are some deeply nested code in Autoware. Deeply nested code is difficult to read and understand. You can reduce nest for some patterns. Please consider reducing nest when you write deeply nested code(In general, more than 3-4 nested blocks).

For example.

``` c
int ret = some_function(a, b, c);
if (ret < 0) {
   log("error....");
} else {
  // success case
}
```

``` c
int ret = some_function(a, b, c);
if (ret < 0) {
   log("error....");
   return ret;
}

// success case
```

Other example(conditions in loop)

``` c
while (some_iterations()) {
    int ret = some_function(a, b, c);
    if (ret < 0) {
       log("error....");
    } else {
      // success case
    }
}
```

``` c
while (some_iterations()) {
    int ret = some_function(a, b, c);
    if (ret < 0) {
       log("error....");
       continue; // or break, return
    }

    // success case
}
```

Please consider

See also
- https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Computer_Programming/Coding_Style/Minimize_nesting
- Art of Readable code Section 7 Minimize Nesting(日本語版: 7.7 ネストを浅くする)
- Code Complete Section 4
